TY  - JOUR
T1  - Job Search and Implicit Contracts
AU  - Cothren, Richard
Y1  - 1983/06/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/261160
DO  - 10.1086/261160
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 494
EP  - 504
VL  - 91
IS  - 3
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - A model incorporating costly search and implicit contracts is examined. The contracts differ from those studied in the traditional literature by allowing for both temporary and permanent layoffs. A natural rate of unemployment is determined, and comparative statics analysis shows that changes in the utility value of leisure, in the cost of search, and in the dispersion of prices each have an ambiguous effect on this natural rate.
AB  - A model incorporating costly search and implicit contracts is examined. The contracts differ from those studied in the traditional literature by allowing for both temporary and permanent layoffs. A natural rate of unemployment is determined, and comparative statics analysis shows that changes in the utility value of leisure, in the cost of search, and in the dispersion of prices each have an ambiguous effect on this natural rate.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/261160
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/261160
Y2  - 2024/03/22
